341 (1) The number of days to initially respond to the
342 request.
343 (2) The number of days to conduct a repair assessment.
344 (3) Whether the repair assessment was made at the
345 recipient's residence, the repair facility, remotely, or
346 another location.
347 (4) If prior authorization to make the repair was
348 necessary, the number of days to receive the agency
349 determination.
350 (5) The number of days from the repair assessment to
351 order a replacement part.
352 (6) The number of days from the repair assessment to
353 complete repair of the wheelchair, including the number of
354 days to receive any replacement part ordered.
355 (7) Whether the repair was completed at the recipient's
356 residence, the repair facility, or another location.
357 (e) The commissioner shall seek any federal approval
358 necessary, including amendment of the state Medicaid plan or
359 application for a waiver, to implement this section.
360 (f) The commissioner shall adopt rules to implement
361 this section.
