427 (b)(1) An original manufacturer shall make available,
428 directly or through an authorized repair provider and in
429 compliance with the terms required in subsection (c), any
430 documentation, parts, or tools required for the maintenance or
431 repair of a motorized wheelchair to the consumer or an
432 independent repair provider.
433 (2) The duty described in subdivision (1) includes,
434 with respect to an electronic security lock or other
435 security-related function, the provision of any documentation,
436 tools, or parts required to access and reset the lock or
437 function when disabled during the maintenance or repair of a
438 motorized wheelchair.
439 (3) The required documentation, parts, or tools may be
440 provided to a consumer or independent repair provider through
441 an appropriate secure release system.
442 (c) An original manufacturer shall fulfill the duty
443 imposed in subsection (b) in good faith, which means in
444 accordance with the minimum terms required in this subsection.
445 (1) Documentation shall be provided at no charge except
446 for the actual cost of preparing and sending a physical copy.
447 (2) Parts shall be provided on the same terms as would
448 apply to an authorized repair provider, including all of the
